Calling a DLL using Watcom

    This examples shows how to call a Watcom 32-bit linear executable DLL
    from a Watcom 32-bit linear executable program.  The example uses the
    DOS/4G API to load the DLL using either of two methods: an IMPLIB, to
    cause the DLL to be loaded at program load time, or dynamically, using
    the DOS/4G D32LoadModule API call.

    The example consists of the following files in the EXAMPLES\DLL\WATCOM
    directory:

    MYDLL.C     C source for DLL example code.
    
    CALLER.C    C source file for calling DLL functions in MYDLL.

    MAKEFILE    Polymake-configured makefile to build all the example
                executables using Watcom.
